    <briefdescription>
<para>Description of a Tensor layout in memory. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Each logical tensor is embedded in both global and local memories within some enclosing physical tensors.</para>
<para>This embedding is referred to as &apos;layout&apos;, which specifies the actual distance in elements between the start of consecutive data elements in each dimension.</para>
<para>For the first axis the distance is always 1 element and and so this value is not stored.</para>
<para>line_length and plane_area in memory, in units of an element. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
